article:
This is a list of the heads of government of the modern Greek state, from its
establishment during the Greek Revolution to the present day. Although
various official and semi-official appellations were used during the early
decades of independent statehood, the title of '[[Prime Minister of
Greece|Prime Minister]]' has been the formal designation of the office at
least since 1843. Note that the numbering system in the list is arbitrary and
has no official status.
